          "title": "*I will make up to you for the years* — restoration as reversal",
          "body": "Verses 19-27 unfold the restoration as a point-by-point reversal of the devastation. The locusts ate the grain, new wine, and oil (1:10); Yahweh sends grain, new wine, and oil (2:19). The land was wilderness (2:3); the pastures turn green (2:22). The fig tree and vine were stripped (1:7); they yield in full (2:22). The northern army devoured; the northern army is dispersed (2:20). The climactic promise is 2:25 — *I will make up to you for the years that the swarming locust has eaten*. Yahweh does not merely stop the damage; He restores the timeline itself. The four locust-names of 2:25 echo 1:4, framing the entire crisis as something Yahweh personally underwrites and personally undoes. The doubled refrain — *My people will never be put to shame* (2:26-27) — uses the same *never again* formula Yahweh spoke after the Flood (Genesis 9:11), elevating restoration to covenantal permanence."
